@node "Overview" "Overview of PowerView"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Main"
@{b}PowerView@{ub} is a JPEG-picture viewer for the Amigacomputer
for those of you who owns a PPC-accelerator (ppc.library). The
JPEG conversion is based upon libjpeg V6b from the Independent
JPEG Group.

I guess that's all, now enjoy!
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installing PowerView"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Overview"
Not much to say here really.

∑ Copy the executable to wherever you want it!

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements of PowerView"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Installation"
PowerView requires:
 ∑ Workbench and Kickstart @{b}38+@{ub}
 ∑ ppc.library @{b}46.19+@{ub}
 ∑ PPC-accelerator

@{i}PowerView has been tested on the following setup:
 ∑ A1200T/040@25MHz+603@240MHz/BVision/64Mb Fast
 ∑ A1200/EC040@25MHz+603@160MHz/16 Mb Fast
@{ui}
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Using PowerView"
@next "License"
@prev "Requirements"
CLI Usage:
  @{b}PowerView FILENAME DEPTH/N SCREENMODE/K CENTER/K@{ub}

  @{b}FILENAME@{ub}     The name of the jpegfile to view
  @{b}DEPTH@{ub}        Nr of bitplanes to use (3 - 8)
  @{b}SCREENMODE@{ub}   Forces the screenmoderequester
  @{b}CENTER@{ub}       Center the image

  If the program is started from CLI and not all required
  variables is given (at this point it's even not possible)
  the program will read the tooltypes anyway and try to use
  the values used. If the DEPTH, MODEID, WIDTH and HEIGHT
  tooltypes are not specified an ASL requester will appear.

  The FILENAME can also be left blank when run from CLI and
  a ASL filerequester will ask for you're desired file.

ToolTypes:
  @{b}WIDTH@{ub}        The screen width
  @{b}HEIGHT@{ub}       The screen height
  @{b}DEPTH@{ub}        Nr of bitplanes (3-8)
  @{b}MODEID@{ub}       Preferred modeid
  @{b}SCREENMODE@{ub}   Force the screenmoderequester
  @{b}CENTER@{ub}       Center the image

  If the WIDTH, HEIGHT, DEPTH and MODEID tooltypes an not
  set a ASL moderequester will appear. When run the program
  is started from WB a filerequester will always be used to
  specify the JPEG to render.

  Quit the program by either pressing one of the mousebuttons
  or by pressing the q or escape key.

@endnode

