@node "History" "History"
@next "Future"
@prev "Author"

  I wanted to have the CGFX-support ready for this release, but
  due to no way of calling the CGFX-libraries I have to do alot of
  more work on it than I'd expected.

  Since I removed the CENTER option in the last release and I now have
  implemented it again I thought you guys wanted it now.

V0.2b   1999-01-25
  ∑ The CENTER option is woring again
  ∑ The version string is right this time

V0.2   1999-01-25
  ∑ To quit the program you can now press any of the
    mousebuttons, q or escape
  ∑ Removed the profiler compiler option :)
  ∑ Memory requirements is now less than before, due to no more
    memory is allocated than needed to display the picture
  ∑ Autoscrolling added
  ∑ The CENTER option is right now not working, but it will probaly
    fixed later on.

V0.1b  1999-01-20
  ∑ Improved the CLI-argument & WB-ToolTypes parsing

V0.1   1999-01-19
  ∑ First public beta
@endnode

@node "Future" "Future"
@next "Credits"
@prev "History"

I might include (no special order):

  ∑ Grayscale/coloroption
  ∑ GFX-card support (CGFX)

I'm working on support for atleast 24-bit displays using CGFX, but
since there are no (ppc)includes for the library it might take some
time for me to implement it.

If you have any suggestions, please @{"contact" link "Author" 0} me!
@endnode

